    "updated_at": "2019-02-06T03:15:52Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I was wrong :D\r\nThe chttp2 transport has checks to not return the op GRPC_OP_RECV_CLOSE_ON_SERVER till the underlying stream is unavailable for both reading and writing.\r\n\r\nThis means that on the server side, we will get back the CompletionOp when -\r\n1) a RST_STREAM (cancel) renders the stream closed for both reading and writing\r\n2) The server sends the status which would be the end of the RPC\r\n\r\nWell, that was unnecessary time spent on this :D"
